  "text": "According to [CITATION_1] , some traits of the individual, such as personality, work context, and the interaction between these two traits, influence behavior through motivational states. Contextual factors, namely organizational climate and leadership, motivate individuals to undertake actions entailing a high potential risk, generating on organizational members cognitive-motivational states that drive them to undertake change-oriented behaviors [CITATION_2] .",
